Adjust the blocks to swap based on your VRAM, this is a tradeoff between speed and memory usage.

Alternatively there's option to use VRAM management introduced in DiffSynt-Studios. This is usually slower, but saves even more VRAM compared to BlockSwap
If you have Triton installed, connect this for ~30% speed increase

fp8_fast seems to cause huge quality degradation

fp_16_fast enables "Full FP16 Accmumulation in FP16 GEMMs" feature available in the very latest pytorch nightly, this is around 20% speed boost. 

Sageattn if you have it installed can be used for almost double inference speed
Input can be nothing for text2vid, a single image for image2vid or any number of frames for video extension
Number of frames to continue from for the next extension

A grand Roman bathhouse interior, richly detailed with marble columns, intricate Roman mosaics on the walls and floors, and a luxurious atmosphere of steam and soft light. In the center, a slightly overweight Roman emperor with medium-length curly hair lounges in an elevated marble bathtub, looking relaxed and regal. Around him, large pools of the Roman thermae are visible, scattered with fruit bowls, golden pitchers, and lounging Roman citizens in togas or undressing for the bath. Some are already in the water, chatting or reclining on stone benches. Classical architecture, natural light from oculus openings above, historical realism, cinematic composition, photorealistic, soft focus depth, shot on 35mm lens. camera is pulling back to reveal the large space of Roman baths,
